---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Commercial Door Services Orlando, FL | 24/7 Repair & Install"
  description="Commercial door installation, repair, and 24/7 emergency service in Orlando, FL. Storefront, automatic, fire-rated, and high-security doors for Downtown, Lake Nona, International Drive, Winter Park, Dr. Phillips & more. Call (954) 727-5435."
  keywords="commercial door services Orlando, commercial door repair Orlando FL, commercial door installation Orlando, storefront door repair Orlando, automatic door repair Orlando, fire-rated doors Orlando, commercial locksmith Orlando, 24/7 commercial door Orlando, hurricane impact doors Orlando, Lake Nona commercial door, International Drive commercial door, Winter Park commercial door, Downtown Orlando commercial door"
>
  <section class="relative bg-primary text-white py-20 md:py-28 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-cover bg-center opacity-20" style="background-image: url('/images/services/hero.webp')" role="img" aria-label="Commercial door services in Orlando Florida"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-primary/95 to-primary/70"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <a href="/" class="hover:text-white">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">›</span> <span class="text-white">Orlando, FL</span>
        </nav>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-6xl tracking-wide mb-4">Commercial Door Services in Orlando, FL</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-200 mb-8">Storefront, automatic, fire-rated, and high-security door installation, repair, and maintenance for businesses across Downtown Orlando, Lake Nona, International Drive, Winter Park, Dr. Phillips, and the rest of Central Florida. 24/7 emergency response.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="tel:9547275435" class="bg-white text-primary font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors text-center">(954) 727-5435</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-white hover:text-primary transition-colors text-center">FREE ESTIMATE</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4">Commercial Door Specialists for Central Florida</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Orlando is one of the highest-foot-traffic commercial markets in the United States. Theme-park hotels, the Orange County Convention Center, retail along International Drive, the Mall at Millenia, and the Orlando International Premium Outlets see door cycle counts most cities never approach. Combine that with humidity, summer thunderstorms, and a hurricane season that demands wind-rated assemblies — and standard hardware fails fast.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Our Orlando crews specialize in commercial-grade <a href="/service/commercial-door-installation" class="text-accent hover:underline">door installation</a>, emergency <a href="/service/commercial-door-repair" class="text-accent hover:underline">door repair</a>, and preventive maintenance built for Florida's hospitality, retail, healthcare, and logistics sectors. We work with hollow metal, aluminum storefronts, automatic sliders and swingers, fire-rated assemblies, hurricane-impact doors, rolling steel service doors, and high-security entries — for retailers along Sand Lake Road and Orange Avenue, restaurants in Thornton Park and Mills 50, medical campuses near Orlando Health and AdventHealth, warehouses around Orlando International Airport (MCO) and the Orange Blossom Trail corridor, and office tenants throughout Downtown and Lake Nona's Medical City.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">When a panic device fails on a Saturday night near Lake Eola, when a tropical storm shreds an aluminum storefront on I-Drive, or when a high-cycle automatic sliding door at Mall at Millenia dies during peak traffic — we respond. 24/7. Locally dispatched. Stocked for the most common commercial hardware brands the day we arrive.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="/images/services/hero.webp" alt="Commercial door installation and repair team serving Orlando, Florida" class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-light">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">Commercial Door Services We Provide in Orlando</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">From a stuck back-of-house service door at a Disney Springs restaurant to a full storefront retrofit on Park Avenue in Winter Park, we handle the full lifecycle of commercial entry hardware.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          { name: "Commercial Door Installation", href: "/service/commercial-door-installation", desc: "New construction and replacement: hollow metal, aluminum storefront, automatic, hurricane-impact, and fire-rated assemblies." },
          { name: "Commercial Door Repair", href: "/service/commercial-door-repair", desc: "Sagging doors, broken closers, damaged frames, storm-damaged panels, failed weatherstrip — fixed fast." },
          { name: "Commercial Door Lock Services", href: "/service/commercial-door-lock-services", desc: "Mortise locks, exit devices, electric strikes, master key systems, access control integration." },
          { name: "Lock Repair", href: "/service/lock-repair", desc: "Sticking cylinders, broken keys, jammed panic bars — rapid response for Orlando businesses." },
          { name: "Hinge Repair & Replacement", href: "/service/hinge-repair-replacement", desc: "Continuous hinges, ball-bearing butts, pivot sets — reset for proper alignment and load." },
          { name: "Roller Replacement & Frame Repair", href: "/service/roller-replacement-and-frame-repair", desc: "Sliding-door rollers, tracks, and bent frames straightened or replaced." },
        ].map((s) => (
          <a href={s.href} class="group block bg-white rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300 border border-gray-border/30 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-2">{s.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">{s.desc}</p>
            <p class="text-accent text-sm font-heading tracking-wide">Learn More →</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">Industries We Serve in Orlando</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">Different businesses, different door problems. Here is how we tailor commercial door services to Orlando's largest commercial sectors.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Hospitality & Theme-Park Adjacent</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Hotels along International Drive, near Universal Orlando, around Lake Buena Vista, and the Orange County Convention Center take 24/7 traffic. We service guest entry doors, automatic operators, electronic access systems, and stairwell fire-doors with minimal disruption to operations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Retail & Storefront</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">High-cycle aluminum storefront and automatic sliding doors at the Mall at Millenia, Orlando International Premium Outlets, Florida Mall, Disney Springs, and Park Avenue in Winter Park need heavy-duty closers, replaced bottom rails, and re-glazed storefront panels — usually without closing the shop.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Restaurants & Bars</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Restaurants in Thornton Park, Mills 50, the Milk District, and Winter Park need code-compliant exit devices, reliable back-of-house service doors, and walk-in cooler hardware that survives Florida humidity and constant temperature swings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Medical & Healthcare</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Medical offices in Lake Nona's Medical City, around Orlando Health Downtown, AdventHealth campuses, and Nemours require ADA-compliant automatic operators, hands-free actuation, and fire-rated stairwell assemblies. We handle annual fire-door inspections and hardware retrofits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Warehouse & Logistics</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Distribution centers near Orlando International Airport (MCO), the Orange Blossom Trail corridor, and the 408/Beachline industrial belt rely on rolling steel service doors, hurricane-rated hollow metal entries, and dock-area pedestrian doors. We rebuild fork-truck-hit jambs and replace storm-damaged frames.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-light p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl text-primary mb-2">Office Towers & Mixed-Use</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Class-A office tenants in Downtown Orlando, around Lake Eola, the SunTrust Center area, and emerging mixed-use developments in Lake Nona need reliable revolving doors, stairwell fire-doors, tenant-suite cylinders, and master key system management.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-light">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-3">Orlando Neighborhoods & Service Areas We Cover</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">Local crews dispatched across Greater Orlando. If you are inside the I-4 / 408 / 417 / 528 envelope, we are likely already on a job near you today.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
        {[
          "Downtown Orlando","Thornton Park","Mills 50","Lake Eola Heights","SoDo","Baldwin Park","College Park","Audubon Park","Lake Nona","Medical City","Dr. Phillips","MetroWest","Hunter's Creek","Winter Park","Maitland","Altamonte Springs","Lake Mary","Sanford","Apopka","Ocoee","Winter Garden","Kissimmee","Celebration","International Drive","Universal Area","Lake Buena Vista","Disney Springs","Pine Hills","Orlovista","Conway","Belle Isle","Azalea Park","Pine Castle","MCO Airport Corridor"
        ].map((area) => (
          <span class="bg-white text-gray-700 text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded border border-gray-border/40 text-center">{area}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-sm">Anchored by landmarks like Lake Eola Park, Camping World Stadium, the Amway Center, the Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts, the Orange County Convention Center, Mall at Millenia, Orlando International Premium Outlets, Park Avenue in Winter Park, Disney Springs, Universal CityWalk, and Orlando International Airport (MCO) — plus surrounding suburbs along I-4, the 408 East-West Expressway, the 417 Greeneway, the 528 Beachline, and Orange Blossom Trail.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-10">Why Orlando Businesses Choose Us</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Local, Not a Call Center</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Technicians who know I-Drive traffic adds 30 minutes during convention weeks, and route around it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Storm-Ready Specs</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Hurricane-impact glazing, wind-rated frames, corrosion-resistant hardware for Florida humidity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Code-Aware</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Florida Building Code, IBC, NFPA 80, and ADA compliance baked into every install and inspection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center p-6 border border-gray-border/30 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl text-primary mb-2">Real 24/7 Emergency</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">A Saturday night break-in on Sand Lake Road gets a tech on-site, not a Monday voicemail.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-light">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl text-center tracking-wide text-primary mb-10">Orlando Commercial Door FAQs</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          { q: "Do you offer 24/7 emergency commercial door service in Orlando?", a: "Yes. We dispatch emergency commercial door technicians across Greater Orlando 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, including weekends and holidays. Whether your storefront on International Drive was hit overnight, a panic device failed at a Mills 50 restaurant, or a sliding door froze open at a Lake Nona medical office, we respond fast and secure the opening before we leave." },
          { q: "Which Orlando neighborhoods do you serve?", a: "We serve all of Greater Orlando — including Downtown Orlando, Thornton Park, Mills 50, Lake Nona, Dr. Phillips, MetroWest, Winter Park, Maitland, Altamonte Springs, Lake Mary, Sanford, Apopka, Winter Garden, Kissimmee, Celebration, International Drive, Lake Buena Vista, the MCO airport corridor, and points along I-4, the 408, the 417, and the 528." },
          { q: "Do you install hurricane-impact commercial doors in Orlando?", a: "Yes. We install Florida Building Code-approved hurricane-impact storefront systems, wind-rated hollow metal frames, and laminated glazing assemblies — common requests from retailers, restaurants, and office tenants in Central Florida who want one less thing to board up before a storm." },
          { q: "How does Florida humidity affect commercial doors?", a: "Significantly. Humidity accelerates corrosion on door closers, hinges, and threshold hardware. Wood doors swell and bind. Aluminum frames pit when finishes break down. Salt-laden coastal air pulled inland during storms attacks ferrous components. We spec stainless and aluminum hardware where appropriate and use sealed bearings on closer arms." },
          { q: "Are your installations Florida Building Code and ADA compliant?", a: "Yes. Every install is performed to current Florida Building Code, the International Building Code, NFPA 80 for fire-rated assemblies, and ADA accessibility requirements — including operator force, opening speed, threshold height, and clear-opening width." },
          { q: "Do you handle annual fire-door inspections?", a: "Yes. NFPA 80 requires annual inspection and documentation of all fire-rated door assemblies. We perform the inspection, generate compliance documentation, and complete corrective repairs in a single visit when possible — common for Orange County Public Schools facilities, hotels, healthcare buildings, and multi-tenant office towers." },
          { q: "What commercial door brands do you service in Orlando?", a: "We service all major commercial brands including LCN, Norton, Sargent, Von Duprin, Yale, Schlage, Best, Corbin Russwin, Stanley, Besam/Assa Abloy automatic operators, Horton, Record, and rolling steel from Cornell, Cookson, and Wayne Dalton." }
        ].map((faq) => (
          <details class="group bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-border/30">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-heading text-lg tracking-wide text-primary">
              {faq.q}
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-primary text-white text-center">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl tracking-wide mb-4">24/7 Emergency Commercial Door Services in Orlando</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">From a busted entry on Sand Lake Road to a failed automatic operator at a Lake Nona office lobby — call now and an Orlando-based technician will be rolling within minutes.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="tel:9547275435" class="bg-accent text-white font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-blue-800 transition-colors">Call Now (954) 727-5435</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-heading text-xl tracking-wide px-8 py-4 rounded hover:bg-white hover:text-primary transition-colors">FREE ESTIMATE</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Commercial Door Services — Orlando",
    "image": "https://commercial-door-services.com/images/logo.png",
    "url": "https://commercial-door-services.com/location/commercial-door-services-orlando",
    "telephone": "+1-954-727-5435",
    "priceRange": "$$",
    "address": { "@type": "PostalAddress", "addressLocality": "Orlando", "addressRegion": "FL", "addressCountry": "US" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "City", "name": "Orlando" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County, FL" }
    ],
    "openingHoursSpecification": { "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday","Sunday"], "opens": "00:00", "closes": "23:59" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do you offer 24/7 emergency commercial door service in Orlando?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. We dispatch emergency commercial door technicians across Greater Orlando 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, including weekends and holidays. Whether your storefront on International Drive was hit overnight, a panic device failed at a Mills 50 restaurant, or a sliding door froze open at a Lake Nona medical office, we respond fast and secure the opening before we leave." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Which Orlando neighborhoods do you serve?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "We serve all of Greater Orlando — including Downtown Orlando, Thornton Park, Mills 50, Lake Nona, Dr. Phillips, MetroWest, Winter Park, Maitland, Altamonte Springs, Lake Mary, Sanford, Apopka, Winter Garden, Kissimmee, Celebration, International Drive, Lake Buena Vista, the MCO airport corridor, and points along I-4, the 408, the 417, and the 528." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do you install hurricane-impact commercial doors in Orlando?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. We install Florida Building Code-approved hurricane-impact storefront systems, wind-rated hollow metal frames, and laminated glazing assemblies — common requests from retailers, restaurants, and office tenants in Central Florida who want one less thing to board up before a storm." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does Florida humidity affect commercial doors?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Significantly. Humidity accelerates corrosion on door closers, hinges, and threshold hardware. Wood doors swell and bind. Aluminum frames pit when finishes break down. Salt-laden coastal air pulled inland during storms attacks ferrous components. We spec stainless and aluminum hardware where appropriate and use sealed bearings on closer arms." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Are your installations Florida Building Code and ADA compliant?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Every install is performed to current Florida Building Code, the International Building Code, NFPA 80 for fire-rated assemblies, and ADA accessibility requirements — including operator force, opening speed, threshold height, and clear-opening width." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do you handle annual fire-door inspections?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. NFPA 80 requires annual inspection and documentation of all fire-rated door assemblies. We perform the inspection, generate compliance documentation, and complete corrective repairs in a single visit when possible — common for Orange County Public Schools facilities, hotels, healthcare buildings, and multi-tenant office towers." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What commercial door brands do you service in Orlando?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "We service all major commercial brands including LCN, Norton, Sargent, Von Duprin, Yale, Schlage, Best, Corbin Russwin, Stanley, Besam/Assa Abloy automatic operators, Horton, Record, and rolling steel from Cornell, Cookson, and Wayne Dalton." } }
    ]
  })} />
</Layout>
